NAME
    URI::Escape::Path - Like URI::Escape, but does not escape '/'

VERSION
    This document describes version 0.001 of URI::Escape::Path (from Perl
    distribution URI-Escape-Path), released on 2020-06-18.

SYNOPSIS
     use URI::Escape::Path;
     # use like you would use URI::Escape
     my $escaped = uri_escape('/foo bar'); # => "/foo%20bar'

DESCRIPTION
    This module's "uri_escape()" and "uri_escape_utf8()" functions use this
    default unsafe character list:

     "^A-Za-z0-9\-\._~"

    instead of URI::Escape's default of:

     "^A-Za-z0-9\-\._~"

FUNCTIONS
  uri_escape
  uri_escape_utf8
  uri_unescape
HOMEPAGE
    Please visit the project's homepage at
    <https://metacpan.org/release/URI-Escape-Path>.

